Rachael Aladi Ayegba (amụrụ na 25 June 1986) bụ onye bụbu onye Naijirịa na-agba bọọlụ mba ụwa nke ụmụ nwanyị na-agba dịka onye na-edebe goolu
Na klọb, ọ gbara bọọlụ maka ọtụtụ klọb ndị Finland n'etiti afọ 2005 na 2016
Ayegba bụ onye ọkwọ ụgbọala bọs ugbu a na London.

Na Na Naijirịa, Ayegba gbara bọọlụ maka Oladimeji Tigress, Ufouma Babes, FCT Queens nke Abuja, na Edo Queens. N'afọ 2005, Ayegba kwagara Finland, ebe ọ gbara bọọlụ afọ iri na otu. N'oge 2007 FIFA Women's World Cup, ọ gbara bọọlụ maka Kokkolan Palloveikot na Finland. Na Finland, ọ gbakwara Kuopion Palloseura, GBK Kokkola na PK-35 Vantaa bọọlụ. O meriri na 2010, 2011 na 2012 Naisten Liigas na PK-35 Vantaa, yana 2012 na 2013 Finnish Women's Cups.

Ayegba mere nke mbụ ya maka otu egwuregwu bọọlụ ụmụ nwanyị nke mba Naijirịa na egwuregwu 2001 megide Namibia. Ọ hapụrụ 2003 All-Africa Games n'ihi mmerụ ahụ. Ayegba nọchitere anya Naijiria na 2007 FIFA Women's World Cup, yana 2006 na 2008 African Women's Championships, na 2007 All-Africa Games.
Ayegba lara ezumike nká na bọọlụ n'afọ 2016. O mechara rụọ ọrụ dị ka onye nkuzi, wee kwaga London na 2018. Ka ọ na-erule 2021, Ayegba rụrụ ọrụ dị ka onye ọkwọ ụgbọ ala na-azụ maka Go-Ahead London.
